texts.text: >In the cityâ€”
>You and Lindsay fight against the demons flooding the streets.
Begone!
Not yet!
Damn, they just keep coming!
Demons have come through the Dragon Stream many times, but
this is something different.
Like it or not, this means Vanitas is close to waking.
Commander! The civilians we evacuated have arrived on base!
Copy that. Get your people ready to withdraw!
Hurry. Fall behind and you'll end up surrounded by demons.
What's that?
*howl*
Ahaha!
>More demons appear. They target Lindsay and surround her.
A Devil Download? It must be the Elements!
>Your smartphone rings.
[sys user_name], Lindsay Altskan.
We predicted the Dragon Stream disturbance would draw you here.
Set a trap for us, did you? Damn.
To think you'd come here with the Extinction Event so near,

just to protect civilians.
You're far too naive, foolish.
And it will cost you your lives.
This will be your grave.
The commander's surrounded! Get her out! Get her out at any cost!
Heh, heh, heh...
Gah!
You won't escape. It's designed so you can't. You'll die here.
It's past the point where you small fry can help.
With you gone, the Brotherhood of Harmony will lose momentum.
And that means our chances of victory will be all the greater.
Hmph. Don't you underestimate me.
>Lindsay's demon sends an Elements ally flying.
Heh, heh. I must say, not bad.
I once trekked through a desert on reconnaissance. By comparison,
this is almost boring. I might take a nap.
Sorry to have bored you. Let's make this a bit more exciting.
>The Elements summon dozens of demons around Lindsay at once.
I'm coming now!
Don't die!
If you've time to talk, fight.
Hardly as if I need help from the likes of you, anyway.
>Lindsay strikes down her attackers, one after another.
That's the commander for you.
Move! Strike down the demons and clear a path to her!
Here goes!
>The soldiers gather outside the demons encircling Lindsay,
>focusing on a single point to make a path to her.
Gah... Detestable...
*Groan*
Don't stop! Keep going!

Heh, heh... What fools.
Die already!
Heads up!
Gah!
Thanks. You saved me.
>You cut through the demon hoard and finally reach Lindsay.
*pant* *pant*
Let's fight together.
Need a hand?
Oh, for... Enough of the cheek, recruit.
Commander! Let's retreat!
I would have been fine on my own... *groan*
Your breaching from outside the circle was quite unforeseen.
I suppose it must be due to your influence, [sys user_name].
But you're one move too late.
>Darkness gapes beneath Lindsay!
>Several spears rise from below, piercing her in several places.
*gasp*
Commander!
Network summons aren't our only means of attack.
We have several methods of longranged attack.
Times like these are perfect for using the aces up our sleeves.
Demon attacks from above kept you from looking down.
Commander! Commander!
Don't fuss. This is nothing...
Hush, Commander. There's a bloody hole in your stomach!
>Lindsay closes her eyes and hunches over.
>You rush to support her, helping to prop up her injured body.

Ngh, let me go! I don't need...
any pity from you.
You won't be getting away.
>More demons begin to appear, one after another!
>Surrounded by the Elements' demons, everyone prepares to die.
>You, however, continue to mow down demons left and right.
That's... That's absurd. How?
We have no data about this. Just what are you?
>While sustaining heavy damage from the Elements' assault,
you and the others manage to flee Shibuya.
How... disgraceful of me...
